! --------------<DESCRIPTION>-------------------
! Keep in mind that my xmodmap is some clunky result of searching my keymapping so definitely not a neat solution.
! I'm changing left alt key to mode switch and caps lock to alt key becuase who uses caps lock anyway just press the good ol' shift
! Every keyname is represented as capital but not the capital in real use.
! If you want to change xmodmap by your flavor refer to the table in the bottom of this file.
! Also Arch wiki is a great resource.
! https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Xmodmap
!
! Keycode can be detected with xev command just open up your terminal and type xev to find out.
!
! Below is a short description for my keymappings
! n.  <keyname> 		for <explanation>
! 0.  <Alt_L>			for Mode_switch key
! 1.  <Caps_Lock>		for Alt_L key
! 2.  <P>				for Plus
! 3.  <H> 				for home
! 4.  <Colon>(;) 		for end
! 5.  <i, j, k, l> 		for (up, left, down, right) respectively
! 6.  <Y> 				for Esc or escape key
! 7.  <U>				for Backspace key
! 8.  <O>				for Delete key
! 9.  <N>				for Pageup or prior key
! 10. <M>				for Page down or Next key
! 11. <Q>				for Backslash
! 12. <W>				for Equal
! 13. <E>				for Slash
! 14. <R>				for underscore
! 15. <A>				for Ampersand
! 16. <S>				for Asterisk
! 17. <D>				for Dollar
! 18. <F>				for Percentage
! 19. <1>				for exclamation mark
! 20. <2>				for at
! 21. <3>				for numbersign
! 22. <B>				for F6
! 23. <(, )>			for less(<) and greater(>)
! 24. <Z>				for Dash(-)
! 25. <X>				for Dash(>)
! 26. <C>				for Carret(^)
! --------------<DESCRIPTION/>------------------
!
! You should clear special key you want to change bofore assigning 
!
! Clear special keys and reassign
clear mod1
clear lock
keycode 64 = Mode_switch 
keycode 66 = Alt_L 

! Set custom key mapping
! Key code mapping table's format is in the next line.
! keycode <number> = <normal key> <key pressed with shift> <key pressed with mode switch> <key pressed with shift and mode switch>
! --------------------------------------------------------------------
! keycode	|normal			|shift		|mode key		|mode+ shift
! --------------------------------------------------------------------
keycode 33 = p 				P 			plus
keycode 44 = j 				J 			Left
keycode 45 = k 				K 			Down
keycode 31 = i 				I 			Up
keycode 46 = l 				L 			Right
keycode 30 = u 				U 			BackSpace
keycode 32 = o 				O 			Delete
keycode 43 = h 				H 			Home
keycode 29 = y 				Y 			Escape
keycode 47 = semicolon 		colon 		End
keycode 57 = n 				N 			Prior
keycode 58 = m 				M 			Next
keycode 24 = q 				Q 			backslash
keycode 25 = w 				W 			equal
keycode 38 = a 				A 			ampersand
keycode 39 = s 				S 			asterisk
keycode 40 = d 				D 			dollar
keycode 41 = f 				F 			percent
keycode 10 = 1 				exclam 		exclam
keycode 11 = 2 				at 			at
keycode 12 = 3 				numbersign 	numbersign
keycode 56 = b 				B 			F6
keycode 26 = e 				E 			slash
keycode 27 = r 				R 			underscore
keycode 52 = z				Z			minus
keycode 53 = x				X			greater
keycode 54 = c				C			asciicircum
keycode 18 = 9 				parenleft 	less 			
keycode 19 = 0 				parenright 	greater 		
! --------------------------------------------------------------------

! and after assinging you sould assign functionatly again
! Still doesn't get about the mechanism in here, but it works anyway... so yeah
add lock = Caps_Lock
add mod1 = Alt_L Alt_R



